article.headline: Akron 78, N. Carolina A&amp,T 61
article.story: AKRON, Ohio -- Anthony Hitchens scored 23 points and led Akron's second-half surge as the Zips pulled away to beat North Carolina A&T 78-61 Saturday night. Brett McKnight had 13 points and Nate Linhart had 11 for Akron (6-3). Ed Jones had 23, and Tavarus Alston had 15 for the Aggies (5-4). Akron trailed most of the first half, which ended in a tie at 35. But a 7-0 run at the beginning of the second half that included a 3-pointer by Hitchens put the Zips ahead for good. Another 3-pointer by Hitchens gave Akron its biggest lead at 78-59 with 3:56 to play. Hitchens was 6-of-8 from behind the 3-point arc as Akron repeatedly fired from long range but hit just 13 of 36.
